| **Disease**                    | **Symptoms**                                  | **Diagnosis**                          | **Treatment**                                | **Image**                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |
| ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Peste des Petits Ruminants** | Fever, discharge, ulcers, diarrhea, pneumonia | Clinical signs, ELISA, PCR             | Supportive care, antibiotics, vaccination    | ![PPR](https://www.fao.org/3/y4385e/y4385e0f.jpg)                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| **Sheep Pox**                  | Fever, pustules, scabs, respiratory signs     | Clinical signs, PCR, virus isolation   | Supportive care, vaccination                 | ![Sheep Pox](https://www.cabi.org/isc/FullTextPDF/2020/20203282188.jpg)                                                                                                                                                             |
| **Bluetongue**                 | Facial swelling, oral ulcers, lameness        | Clinical signs, ELISA, PCR             | Supportive care, vector control, vaccination | ![Bluetongue](https://www.msdvetmanual.com/-/media/manual/veterinary/images/sheep_blue_tongue.jpg)                                                                                                                                  |
| **FMD**                        | Mouth/foot blisters, drooling, lameness       | Clinical signs, virus isolation, ELISA | Supportive care, vaccination                 | ![FMD](https://www.fao.org/4/Y4385E/y4385e04.jpg)                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| **Orf (Ecthyma)**              | Scabby lesions on lips, nostrils, teats       | Clinical signs, PCR                    | Self-limiting, antiseptics, vaccination      | ![Orf](https://www.thevetexpert.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Orf-in-Sheep.jpg)                                                                                                                                                    |
| **Enterotoxaemia**             | Sudden death, diarrhea, abdominal pain        | Postmortem, toxin detection            | Prevention by vaccination                    | ![Enterotoxaemia](https://www.vetlexicon.com/media/k1lcno1v/clostridialenterotoxaemia.jpg)                                                                                                                                          |
| **Anthrax**                    | Sudden death, bleeding from orifices          | Blood smear, culture                   | Early antibiotics, vaccination               | ![Anthrax](https://www.fao.org/3/y4385e/y4385e07.jpg)                                                                                                                                                                               |
| **Brucellosis**                | Abortions, infertility, weak lambs            | Serology, culture                      | No cure; culling, biosecurity                | ![Brucellosis](https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Syed-Abdul-Wahab/publication/332774847/figure/fig2/AS:756764235456512@1556663182722/Placenta-showing-cotyledons-covered-with-yellow-mucoid-material-in-Brucella-melitensis.ppm) |
| **Listeriosis**                | Circling, head tilt, abortion                 | Culture, clinical signs                | High-dose penicillin or tetracycline         | ![Listeriosis](https://www.fao.org/3/y4385e/y4385e05.jpg)                                                                                                                                                                           |
| **Caseous Lymphadenitis**      | Lymph node abscesses                          | Culture, PCR                           | Drain abscesses, cull chronic cases          | ![CLA](https://www.abc.net.au/cm/lb/8913886/data/cla-disease-image-data.jpg)                                                                                                                                                        |
| **Pasteurellosis**             | Fever, nasal discharge, sudden death          | Clinical signs, culture                | Antibiotics (penicillin, oxytetracycline)    | ![Pasteurellosis](https://www.merckvetmanual.com/-/media/manual/veterinary/images/sheep_pasteurella.jpg)                                                                                                                            |
| **Foot Rot**                   | Foul smell, hoof separation, lameness         | Clinical signs                         | Foot trimming, antiseptic baths, antibiotics | ![Foot Rot](https://www.agric.wa.gov.au/sites/gateway/files/styles/original/public/Foot%20rot%20in%20sheep.jpg)                                                                                                                     |
| **Haemonchosis**               | Anemia, bottle jaw, weakness                  | Fecal exam, FAMACHA, clinical signs    | Anthelmintics, supportive care               | ![Haemonchus](https://cdn.britannica.com/18/94118-050-30E0C5A6/Haemonchus-contortus.jpg)                                                                                                                                            |
| **Fascioliasis**               | Anemia, bottle jaw, weight loss               | Fecal exam, clinical signs             | Triclabendazole                              | ![Liver Fluke](https://www.farmersjournal.ie/cms_media/module_img/3458/1726307_1_articlelarge_fasciola.jpg)                                                                                                                         |
| **Coccidiosis**                | Bloody diarrhea, weight loss                  | Fecal exam, clinical signs             | Coccidiostats, supportive care               | ![Coccidiosis](https://www.nadis.org.uk/media/1118/coccidiosis-photo-1.jpg)                                                                                                                                                         |
| **Sheep Scab**                 | Itching, crusts, wool loss                    | Skin scraping, clinical signs          | Injectable/topical insecticides              | ![Sheep Scab](https://www.sruc.ac.uk/media/0dml2u5h/sheep-scab.jpg)                                                                                                                                                                 |
| **Ringworm**                   | Circular crusty skin lesions                  | Microscopy, fungal culture             | Topical antifungals, hygiene                 | ![Ringworm](https://www.thevetexpert.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Ringworm-in-Sheep.jpg)                                                                                                                                          |
| **White Muscle Disease**       | Muscle stiffness, sudden lamb death           | Clinical signs, blood test             | Selenium and Vitamin E injections            | ![WMD](https://www.fwi.co.uk/livestock/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2021/11/sheepmuscle.jpg)                                                                                                                                          |
| **Pregnancy Toxemia**          | Dullness, coma, death before lambing          | Urine ketones, low glucose             | IV glucose, propylene glycol                 | ![Pregnancy Toxemia](https://vetstream.ltd.uk/canis/Respimg/image/thumbs/DY00439fig1.jpg)                                                                                                                                           |
| **Mastitis**                   | Painful, swollen udder, abnormal milk         | Clinical exam, milk test               | Intramammary/systemic antibiotics            | ![Mastitis](https://www.progressivedairy.com/images/stories/2019/10/14/20191014-knight-mastitis-1.jpg)                                                                                                                              |
